The "@" character must be followed by a ":", "(", or a C# identifier.  If you intended to switch to markup, use an HTML start tag, for example:

@if(isLoggedIn) {
    <p>Hello, @user!</p>
}

The "@" character must be followed by a ":", "(", or a C# identifier.  If you intended to switch to markup, use an HTML start tag, for example:

